# Icon System

## HugeIcons Pro Usage

```typescript
import { HugeiconsIcon } from "@hugeicons/react"
import { Tick02Icon, Cancel01Icon } from "@hugeicons-pro/core-stroke-rounded"

<HugeiconsIcon icon={Tick02Icon} size={16} className="size-4" />
```

Re-exported convenience icons: `import { HugeiconsIcon, PinIcon, ... } from "@/lib/icons"`

## Sizing Convention (IMPORTANT)

`className="size-*"` is the canonical sizing mechanism. The `size` prop alone is insufficient because Shadcn's `buttonVariants` applies `[&_svg:not([class*='size-'])]:size-4`, forcing 16px on SVGs without a `size-*` class.

```tsx
<HugeiconsIcon icon={SearchIcon} size={20} className="size-5" />
```

| size prop | Tailwind class |
|-----------|---------------|
| 12 | size-3 |
| 14 | size-3.5 |
| 16 | size-4 (default) |
| 20 | size-5 |
| 24 | size-6 |
| 32 | size-8 |

## Brand Icons

```typescript
import { ClaudeIcon, OpenAIIcon } from "@/components/icons/claude"
import { GeminiIcon } from "@/components/icons/gemini"
```

## Custom Icons

Use `createIcon` from `@/lib/icons` for simple path-based icons.
